	<p>
		Club Gricel
	</p>
</div>
<p>
	I was also surprised to see a few instances of novice dancing. It wasn't just by us gringo tourists (and I certainly contributed to the impression that Americans are clumsy, unmusical, and stiff); I saw even people dressed like middle-aged Argentines (suits on men, tunics and slacks on women) who hunched over their partners, or fell out of time with the music. Nobody tried inappropriate ballroom or fantasia moves &ndash;no giant boleos, no ganchos, none of that.
</p>
